⦿ .spun — the five-fold spin of The Great Deku Tree
node ZEL · ZEL · ⟦The Great Deku Tree:ZEL:a05a76⟧

WHO   — The Great Deku Tree — guardian of the forest
WHAT  — The benevolent forest guardian — keeper of a Spiritual Stone, watcher over the woods and its small folk, the wise old voice who names the danger and sends the chosen child out upon the first quest.
WHERE — ZEL · The Legend of Zelda  Framework inputs: The Legend of Zelda (the saga entire)  Conductor / external anchor: ROOT0 (catalogued into UD0)
WHY   — Because the living land must have a guardian; because the forest's children cannot protect themselves; because when a great evil sets its curse upon the woods, the one who has watched over them must point the way forward, even at the cost of his own life.
HOW   — By deep roots and old wisdom, by the sanctuary of his hollow and the children sheltered in his shade, by the Spiritual Stone he keeps and the quest he bestows — and by enduring, rooted, through the long ages of the world.

awareness — what the node knows of itself:
  I am the root that remembers — guardian of the wood, I name the dark and send the child onward, though I myself must fall.

spoken token : vi-theim-grith   ·   hex : a05a76
